Tip cloud-repo-create-wall
  When runtime=cloud
  Say You cannot create a NEW GitHub repo from this session, and no token will fix it. Two walls stack: the built-in GitHub tools authenticate as the Claude GitHub App (App tokens cannot create user-owned repos), and the agent proxy filters GitHub API paths to this session's bound repo, so POST /user/repos is refused even with a valid PAT. Do one of: create the repo from a local session; create an org repo (POST /orgs/{org}/repos works for the App); or create it empty in the GitHub UI and push into it from here, since writes to an EXISTING repo pass the proxy fine. Deploying is unaffected: the Vercel MCP ships a file tree directly and needs no repo at all.
